<HEADLINE> Diplomatic News Summary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 23 (xinhua) -- Following is a summary on
China's diplomatic news covered today by Home News for Overseas
Service Department of Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
Chinese, Namibian Presidents Hold Talks in Beijing
</P>
<P>
BEIJING -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said in Beijing today
that China is ready to make joint efforts with Namibia to raise
the Sino-Namibian traditional friendship to a new high.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remark during talks with Namibian President Sam
Nujoma, who arrived in China on Monday for a week-long state visit
as Jiang's guest. Nujoma has just arrived in Beijing from a tour
of Jiangxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Meets ROK Delegation
</P>
<P>
BEIJING -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin this afternoon held a
meeting in Beijing with a delegation of businessmen from the Korea
Chamber of Commerce and Industry (KCCI) of the Republic of Korea
(ROK), led by its chairman Kim Sang-Ha.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the KCCI, as ROK's largest economic
organisation, has always paid much attention to the development of
relations with China, and made great efforts to promote economic
and trade links.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan Meets Chairman of Nestle
</P>
<P>
BEIJING -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) National Committee, held
a meeting today in Beijing with Helmut Maucher, chairman of Nestle
S.A. of Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
During friendly talks at the Great Hall of the People, Li
thanked Maucher for the hospitality accorded him during his visit
to the headquarters of the famous coffee and food company on his
recent tour of Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan Meets Princess Vadhana of Thailand
</P>
<P>
BEIJING-- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), said
today in Beijing that the Sino-Thai relationship is good, and will
be better in the future.
</P>
<P>
He was speaking during a meeting at the Great Hall of the
People with Princess Galyani Vadhana, sister of the King of
Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Meets US Visitors
</P>
<P>
BEIJING-- Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing met with Richard
Finn, deputy chief executive officer of the Trans America
Corporation(TAC) and chairman of the board of the TAC Leasing, and
his party Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
They exchanged views on co-operation between the two sides on
container leasing and containerized traffic.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Meets ICIE Delegation
</P>
<P>
BEIJING -- Chinese Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo met with a
delegation from the International Congress of Industrialists and
Entrepreneurs (ICIE) here today.
</P>
<P>
Wu commented that Russia-based ICIE has established good
relations with China Association for International Friendly
Contacts, and with China's industrial and business circles.
</P>
</TEXT>
