<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brisk 80th China Export Commodity Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 23 (Xinhua) -- More than 2.5 billion US
dollars worth of contracts have been signed during the first week
at the 80th Chine Export Commodity Fair, which opened October 15
in Guangzhou, capital of south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Machinery products led all export commodities with its 460
million US dollars of business turnover during the October 15-22
period, rising nearly 13 percent over the previous fair.
</P>
<P>
Both trade volume of handicrafts and textiles, as well as
garments, also saw a big rise, reaching 678 million US dollars and
659 million US dollars, respectively.
</P>
<P>
During the fair, China exported the largest volume of
commodities to European Union countries, followed by Hong Kong,
Macao, the United States, countries in southeast Asia, and Japan.
</P>
<P>
Export prices of many products, including rosin, mint oil,
honey, bicycles, electric fans and talcum, lifted by a big margin,
and expected to help export-conducting enterprises increase
economic returns.
</P>
<P>
New, hi-tech and high-value-added products saw a big increase
among export trade volume over previous fairs. The Legend Computer
company conducted 19 million US dollars of business volume during
the first day trading at the fair.
</P>
<P>
Home-made name-brand products also enjoyed growing favor among
buyers abroad.
</P>
<P>
The fair, which has attracted more than 33,500 business people
from 138 countries and regions, is scheduled to end on October
30.
</P>
<P>
China Export Commodity Fair, held twice annually in Guangzhou,
is the country's largest, and highest level international trade
event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
