<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stock Investors Top 10 million in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 23 (Xinhua) -- More than 10 million Chinese
people have invested on its largest stock market in Shanghai, the
largest city in East China.
</P>
<P>
"The number of stock investors rocketed as a result of the
bullish stock market," stock analysts said. They added that the
market sentiment has remained sound this year, due to the
favorable performance of the national economy, and the timely
measures the municipal government has taken to encourage a healthy
market.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the number of stock investors has been
soaring by an average 21,276 a day since May 13, from the eight
million accounts already in existence on that day.
</P>
<P>
Among the investors who have opened accounts on Shanghai's
stock market, about 75 percent live outside Shanghai, up from the
67 percent for 1995.
</P>
<P>
To cope with the increasing number of investors, stock
registration companies in Beijing, Guangdong, Jiangxi, Zhejiang
and Hubei, have begun to offer registration services, even during
weekends and weekday nights. 
</P>
</TEXT>
