<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia to Popularize Family Planning Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia plans to expand
family planning services to 44 percent of the population from the
current four percent in the next two decades.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed today by the consortium of non-governmental
family planning organizations in Nazret, 90 km southeast of Addis
Ababa.
</P>
<P>
The organizations are providing the training courses across
the east African country to expand the coverage of family
planning services.
</P>
<P>
The consortium comprises 27 welfare organizations in the
country, which has a population of 56 million, the second largest
in sub-Sahara Africa after Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
According to the United Nations Children Fund, Ethiopia's
population will double in less than 25 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
