<HEADLINE> 2,600 Trucks Hijacked in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 2,600 trucks were
hijacked in South Africa during the past 12 months, an official
figure released today said.
</P>
<P>
The figure was released by Minister of Safety and Security
Sydney Mufamadi in reply to a question raised in parliament in
Cape Town.
</P>
<P>
He said Gauteng province, which incorporates South Africa's
industrial and commercial heartland around the Johannesburg area,
was worst hit.
</P>
<P>
He said car hijacking in Gauteng alone out-numbers all the
other provinces put together.
</P>
<P>
The Gauteng police announced yesterday that they have arrested
400 most-wanted criminals during the past four months.
</P>
<P>
The arrests were part of the national anti-crime plan which
came into effect in the second week of June this year. 
</P>
