<HEADLINE> S. Africa's New Abortion Bill Adopted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 23 (Xinhua) -- The health Committee of
the South African Parliament today adopted a controversial bill
providing for abortion on demand.
</P>
<P>
The bill contains a clause allowing an abortion for social ad
economic reasons up to the 20th week of pregnancy.
</P>
<P>
The Termination of Pregnancy Bill was adopted by the
parliament committee after more than one week of public hearings
and political debates.
</P>
<P>
It is expected to come up for debate in the South African
Assembly before the end of this month.
</P>
<P>
The governing African National Congress and the Pan-africanist
Congress of Azania support the bill.
</P>
<P>
But it is opposed by the National Party, the Inkatha Freedom
Party, the Freedom Front and the Christian Democratic party.
</P>
