<HEADLINE> Romania Hopes to Join NATO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Romania hopes, with United
States' help, to be in the first group of the former Warsaw Pact
states to enter NATO.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Romanian Foreign Ministry said Romania was
greatly interested in the statement by U.S. President Bill Clinton
Tuesday on NATO's proposed eastward expansion.
</P>
<P>
Clinton called for an expansion of NATO by accepting former
Soviet bloc nations by the end of 1999, the 50th anniversary of
the Western alliance.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian spokesman said the U.S. policy on NATO's eastward
expansion was in conformity with Romania's policy to join the
military organization.
</P>
<P>
He said Clinton's statement, for the first time, defined the
timing and prospects for those nations in central and eastern
Europe eager to join NATO. 
