<HEADLINE> EC Wants Effective Implementation of Environmental Laws </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, October 23 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission (EC)
said today that effective implementation of European Union (EU)
environmental laws is now at a crucial stage.
</P>
<P>
The failure to implement the EU's environmental laws was likely
to put at risk the organization's credibility with its citizens
and its future environmental policy, said the EC in a communique.
</P>
<P>
The document, on how to improve the implementation of the EU
environmental legislation, analyzed the difficulties and
deficiencies in implementing the laws in its member countries.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, the EC registered a total of 265 suspected breaches of
the EU's environmental laws. 
</P>
</TEXT>
