<HEADLINE> Mongella Urges African Countries to Cherish </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 23 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. Under Secretary
on Women and Development Issues, Getrude Mongella, today urged
African nations to cherish the Beijing conference spirit by
empowering women in various position of leadership and
guaranteeing them political and social rights in the society.
</P>
<P>
The official Daily News quoted Mongella as saying at the
University of Dar es Salaam that empowering of women was vital if
the African countries were to realize development changes.
</P>
<P>
The under secretary cautioned that African nations would
continue to experience development legacy if they would neglect
the concept.
</P>
<P>
She appealed to African governments to initiate deliberate
strategies for uplifting women education standards to enable them
to fair favourably in various fields and participate effectively
in the social, economic and political activities.
</P>
<P>
The under secretary said the more the african women were
educated the less infant mortality rate.
</P>
<P>
She said that when women were addressing their issues, "they
were not intending to stage a coup detat against any government".
</P>
<P>
Mongella said empowering women was the only way to bring in
green revolution to African countries, to bridge up the
socialization process gap and end women suppression in the
continent.
</P>
<P>
"We do not want the men of yesterday but we also do not need
women of today who rush for tomorrow. We want equal relations
between men and women, that is all," stressed the under
secretary.
</P>
<P>
She also called upon African governments to ensure women's
rights of land ownership through formation of good land policies
and enacting of favourable inheritance laws to enable women to
get access to various properties.  enditem

