<HEADLINE> Tanzania Owes Big Sum to Desert Agency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR Es SALAAM, October 23 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzania government
owes the Desert Locust Control Organization (DLCO) 414 million
U.S. Dollars as an outstanding contribution to it.
</P>
<P>
Minister for Agriculture and Cooperativen Paul Kimiti said here
today that the government is ready to pay the sum but has failed
to do so due to economic constraints.
</P>
<P>
The Tanzania News Agency quoted Kimiti as telling visiting
Chairman of DLCO Tesfai Ghermazien that the government is
prepared to pay the outstanding contribution between January and
February next year, if economic conditions permit.
</P>
<P>
