in the country to make a follow-up of the Tanzania's
contributions to the DLCO.
</P>
<P>
Minister Kimiti further said the DLCO is important to Tanzania
and that the organization has been in the forefront to assist
Tanzania during locust outbreaks.
</P>
<P>
He cited the recent locust outbreak in Dodoma, Central
Tanzania, where DLCO actively participated in combating the
issue, saying "there was no country which could fight locusts by
its own."
</P>
<P>
Explaining the current financial situation of DLCO, Ghermazien
said the DLCO condition is worse to the extent that it has failed
to pay salaries to its workers for the past six months. 
</P>
