<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets Namibian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng said
today that the Chinese government is confident about the further
consolidation and development of Sino-Namibian traditional
friendship and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Li was speaking in Beijing during a meeting with Namibian
President Sam Nujoma.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting with "his old friend", Li recalled their
meeting in September 1992, when Nujoma visited China, saying that
they had a very good meeting then, and that the successful visit
had promoted the development of Sino-Namibian friendship and
bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Four years have passed since then, Li continued, adding that
Nujoma's current visit indicates that he attaches importance to
the development of bilateral friendship and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Li said he believes that the current visit is certain to
contribute to the enhancement of mutual understanding, and promote
even more bilateral cooperations in various fields.
</P>
<P>
Nujoma talked about his important and fruitful talks yesterday
with his Chinese counterpart Jiang Zemin, saying that both sides
agreed to support each other in politics and diplomacy, and
decided to expand bilateral friendly cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Nujoma said he views his current visit as one of significance.
</P>
<P>
Li noted that China and Namibia, although far away from each
other, established brotherly relations with mutual trust long ago,
which has enabled them to share weal and woe.
</P>
<P>
As early as the time when the Namibian people were struggling
for national independence, the Chinese Communist Party had good
relations with the South West Africa People's Organization, noted
Li.
</P>
<P>
Since the two countries established diplomatic relations, Li
went on to say, the two countries have conducted effective
cooperation in various fields, on the basis of mutual respect,
equality and reciprocity.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that China values Sino-Namibian traditional
friendship, and pays much attention to the development of sincere,
friendly, equal, united and cooperative ties with Namibia, aiming
at a common development.
</P>
<P>
Nujoma reiterated that his country adheres to a "one China"
policy, and opposes any attempt to create "two Chinas" or "one
China, one Taiwan".
</P>
<P>
Expressing his congratulations on the upcoming resumption of
China's sovereignty over Hong Kong and Macao, Nujoma said he hoped
that the Taiwan issue can also be resolved at an early date.
</P>
<P>
Li voiced the Chinese government's appreciation for the
Namibian government's support for China on the Taiwan issue, and
in international affairs, as well as Namibia's support for the
reunification of the motherland of China.
</P>
<P>
On the situation in southern Africa, Nujoma said that Africa
was once a victim of foreign manipulation, and now, there are
still some foreign powers trying to continue their exploitation in
Africa, and save no benefit for African people.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Southern African Development Community is an
organization aiming at development and stability, and it will
cooperate with the Organization of African Unity in removing some
regional unstable elements.
</P>
<P>
He held that the non-aligned movement should be strengthened,
and his country appreciates China's participation in the movement
as an observer, which is a good way of enhancing south-south
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
On state-to-state ties, Li pointed out that China always holds
that it is up to the people of each country to choose their path
to development in accordance with their own conditions, and
opposes any interference in the internal affairs of other
countries by any country, no matter what the reason or excuse.
</P>
<P>
The deeds by some developed countries, which exert pressures on
developing countries by using the means including economic one and
human rights, are bound to meet opposition from most developing
countries, Li said.
</P>
<P>
On UN affairs, Nujoma said the Cold War has come to an end, and
the international community should make joint efforts to give an
end to the fact that the voice of developing countries have been
neglected.
</P>
<P>
Li noted that the status and role of developing countries are
improving, their rational views should be respected by the
international community, and their legal rights and interests
should be guaranteed.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of the Namibian government, Nujoma invited Li and his
wife to visit Namibia at their convenience, and Li accepted the
invitation with pleasure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
