<HEADLINE> Press Urged to Adhere to Correct Guidelines in Public Opinion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Ding Guangen, head of the
Propaganda Department of the Chinese Communist Party Central
Committee, today urged the Chinese press to adhere to correct
guidelines in public opinion, and push the press work onto a new
height.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks at the First Session of the Fifth National
Council of the All-China Journalists' Association which opened
today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Ding, who is also member of the Political Bureau and the
Secretariat of the CPC Central Committee, said that journalists
should strengthen political awareness, bear the overall situation
in mind, and resolutely keep conformity with the Party Central
Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that media work should, while taking economic
construction as the central task, have the overall interests of
the Party and the people in mind, handle relations between
reforms, development and stability in a correct way, and stick to
the viewpoint of belief in the masses. The media should also
increase the attractiveness, instructiveness and persuasiveness of
propaganda work, and build a news contingent with strong political
awareness, high professional competence, good sense of discipline,
and upright working style.
</P>
<P>
He said that the press work is important to the Party and the
people, and that journalism is a lofty and glorious cause.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that this great era of building socialism
with Chinese characteristics has provided ample room for
Chinese journalists to show their abilities.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that journalists should record the profound social
changes, and reflect the all-round vitalization of the Chinese
nation in an honest way, and encourage the people of all
nationalities to plunge into the great practice of reform, opening
up and modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
Ding said that the press has carried out correct guidance in
public opinion over the past few years in general, giving strong
support to the efforts of building a socialist market economic
system, promoting the sustained, rapid and healthy development of
the national economy, and the all-round social progress, and
having created a sound atmosphere for the promotion of socialist
cultural and ethical progress.
</P>
<P>
He added that it is necessary to put a resolute and correct
political orientation in the first place, firmly conduct correct
guidance in public opinion, and adhere to the principle of
"running a newspaper as statesmen".
</P>
<P>
He also called upon journalists to stick to the Party's basic
line and principles, and Deng Xiaoping's theory of building
socialism with Chinese Characteristics, serve the people and
socialism, give priority to positive propaganda, and the interests
of the country as a whole, and conscientiously observe the media
disciplines.
</P>
<P>
The First Session of the Fifth National Council of All-China
Journalists' Association, which will last five days, will discuss
the work report of the Fourth National Council of All-China
Journalists' Association, revise the constitution of the
association, and elect leading figures for the Fifth Council.
</P>
</TEXT>
