<DATE_TIME> 1996-10-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bank of Chinas HKD 4 Billion FRCD Issue Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 24 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China Hong Kong
Branch announced that the signing of its four billion HK dollars
Floating Rate Certificates of Deposit issue was completed today.
</P>
<P>
The FRDC issue has a maturity of five years and carries an
interest rate of 35 basis points over the one-month Hong Kong
Interbank Offered Rate.
</P>
<P>
Because of the overwhelming support extended by the banking
community, there are 61 participating institutions subscribing for
a total amount of 9.3 billion HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
The five-year HK dollar FRCD issue is the largest one raised in
Hong Kong so far; the size of its subscription and the number of
participants are unprecedented.
</P>
<P>
The Japan Bond Research Institute has given an "AA" rating of
the issue while the Hong Kong Monetary Authority has confirmed
acceptance of the issue as eligible collateral under the Liquidity
Adjustment Facility.
</P>
<P>
"For many decades, the Bank of China Hong Kong Branch has been
serving the people of Hong Kong," said Yang Zilin, vice-chairman
of the Bank of China, chief executive of the Bank of China Hong
Kong-Macao Regional Office and general manager of the Bank of
China Hong Kong Branch.
</P>
<P>
"From now on, we will continue to move forward prudently,
carefully maintaining the fine reputation we have built up from
the past, and working closely with various industries for the
ongoing prosperity and stability of Hong Kong," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
