<DOCNO> XIE19961024.0062 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-10-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Offshore Oil Workers Encouraged to Produce More </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 24 (Xinhua) -- China's top leaders have
encouraged the country's offshore petroleum workers to
step up efforts for greater development of the industry.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin, Premier Li Peng, and Vice-Premier Zou
Jiahua wrote to participants in a national conference today to
commend outstanding workers in the offshore oil and gas industry.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin's inscription was, "develop the blue territory, and
promote the offshore petroleum industry".
</P>
<P>
Li Peng's inscription was, "establish a modern enterprise
system, and develop the offshore petroleum industry".
</P>
<P>
The offshore oil and gas industry stands out for its promotion
of national industries with high speed and efficiency, said Vice
Premier Zou Jiahua at the conference.
</P>
<P>
According to Zou, China has signed more than 1000 contracts
with over 60 overseas companies to co-develop offshore oil and
gas, utilizing more than five billion US dollars in direct
overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
As a key energy source, Zou pointed out, oil and gas are of
great significance to China's accomplishment of its development
goals across the century. And exploitation of gas should take
priority because of the growing demand for clean energy.
</P>
<P>
This year, China is expected to produce 14 million tons of
crude oil and three billion cubic meters of natural gas from its
offshore fields. 
</P>
</TEXT>
