<HEADLINE> Myanmar Leader Stresses Non-Interference on UN Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar leader Than Shwe today
urged member countries of the United Nations to scrupulously
refrain, both in words and in deeds, from interference in other
countries' internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
The remarks were contained in his message read by Foreign
Minister U Ohn Gyaw at a ceremony here marking the 51st
anniversary of the UN.
</P>
<P>
