<HEADLINE> Qian: African Nations' Sovereignty Should be Respected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 24 (Xinhua) -- The maintenance of stability in
Africa should rely on the Organization of African Unity (OAU) and
each African country's own efforts, Chinese Vice-Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen said here today.
</P>
<P>
"Every African country's independence and sovereignty should be
respected," he added.
</P>
<P>
Qian expressed the viewpoint during a meeting with Namibian
Foreign Minister Theo-Ben Gurirab, who is accompanying Namibian
President Sam Nujoma on a China trip.
</P>
<P>
Extending a warm welcome to Gurirab, Qian said that President
Nujoma's China visit, which follows Chinese President Jiang
Zemin's visit to Namibia, shows that Sino-Namibian ties are very
close and friendly, and the friendship between the two peoples is
getting closer and closer.
</P>
<P>
Yesterday, Jiang and Nujoma held fruitful talks on developing
bilateral friendly co-cooperation, and they also exchanged views
on international and regional issues of common concern, Qian said,
adding that the two presidents reached an extensive consensus,
voicing that Nujoma's current visit has further strengthened
bilateral friendship and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Agreeing with Qian, Gurirab said that his president is
satisfied with the result of the talks between the two presidents.
</P>
<P>
He said that both countries have a long history, and with joint
efforts, the traditional friendship between the two peoples will
develop continuously.
</P>
<P>
Briefing Qian on the latest situation of southern Africa,
Gurirab stressed that his country devotes itself to the regional
peace and development.
</P>
<P>
In June of this year, the Southern African Development
Community (SADC) established institutions of politics, security
and defense, which will benefit the regional stability, Gurirab
noted.
</P>
<P>
He also mentioned that Namibia fully supports the Five
Principles of Peaceful Co-Existence, and they also can be the
basis for his country's foreign policy and diplomatic efforts.
</P>
<P>
Appreciating Gurirab's briefings, Qian said southern Africa is
continuing its move towards a positive direction, and the region
has come into a new period of seeking stability and development.
</P>
<P>
SADC plays an increasingly important role in advancing regional
economic co-cooperation and development, and it has become a most
vigorous regional organization in Africa, which has attracted the
attention of the international community, Qian noted.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of its politics, security and defense
institutions shows that this organization has been improved, Qian
said, adding that China appreciates the improvement.
</P>
<P>
Qian expressed his belief that the international community
should offer Africa more support and aid, while interfering less,
saying that the turbulence of Africa is mostly the result of
external interference and power politics.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that Namibia adheres to a non-aligned and
good-neighborly foreign policy, plays an active role in
international and regional affairs, and has made its contribution
to regional peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
Qian also expressed his thanks for Namibia's "one China" stance
against any act aiming at creating "two Chinas".  
</P>
</TEXT>
