<HEADLINE> Turkey Seeks Non-Interest Banking System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Turkey's Deputy Prime Minister
and Foreign Minister Tansu Ciller said here that the
"non-interest banking system" advocated by her coalition partner
Welfare Party (RP) would soon be put into practice, local
newspaper Daily News reported today.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted Ciller as saying that a new company to
be set up would give interest-free credits to small and
medium-sized industrial concerns.
</P>
<P>
