"balanced budget," and that this would be tested for the first
time since 1970.
</P>
<P>
For a balanced budget, the tax revenues have been raised from
27 billion U.S. dollars to 32 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The decisive factor in this increase has been the rise in the
number of tax payers, which has gone up from 2 million to 7
million, she said, adding that by the end of the year 1997 the
number of registered tax payers in the country would rise to 20
million. 
