<HEADLINE> Liu Wins Opening Match at World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Olympic Champion Liu Guoliang
rallied from first set deficit to beat Zoran Primorac of Croatia
19-21, 22-20 and 21-12 in the World Cup table tennis tournament in
Nimes, France on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Penholder Liu, also the world championship silver medallist,
trailed Primorac by a game and 20-14 therefore facing six
consecutive match points.
</P>
<P>
But through powerful smashes and an excellent block defence,
the world number three held his nerve to win eight points in a row
to level at one game all.
</P>
<P>
Primorac, World Cup champion three years ago, missed countless
topspins on both wings as he lost his rhythm against his Chinese
opponent in this group b match.
</P>
<P>
Vladimir Samsonov of Belarus, who won the European Masters
title last month, easily swept aside New Zealand's world number
114 Peter Jackson 21-10, 21-13 in just 17 minutes in another
group B game.
</P>
<P>
While in in group a, World number one Kong Linghui of China
