<HEADLINE> 41 PKK Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Forty-one rebels of the
outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were killed in the
military operations staged by the Turkish security forces in
southeastern Turkey, according to two statements issued today.
</P>
<P>
One of the statements, issued by the office of the emergency
rule region, said that the security forces had wiped out 11 PKK
militants in two Turkish border towns of Hakkari province, 12 in
Catak town of Van province, seven in Sirnak province, two in
Diyarbakir province. The security forces also captured three PKK
members in this region, it said.
</P>
<P>
But the statement failed to disclose the time when the PKK
rebels were shot dead or captured.
</P>
<P>
Another statement issued by the office of Erzurum province said
 that the Turkish security forces had killed nine PKK militants
in four-day continuous military operations against the PKK
guerrillas in Erzurum province.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a 12-year-old guerrilla war for
self-rule, which has claimed the lives of more than 21,000 people
including PKK militants, civilians and government troops in
southeastern Turkey since August 1984. 
</P>
