Iranian Deputy Foreign Minister Mohammad Javad Zarif and Russian
Deputy Foreign Minister for Security and Disarmament Georgy
Mamedov.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, the two sides also discussed ways of making
the Middle East region free of weapons of mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
They also exchanged views on the current crises in
Tajikistan, Afghanistan, and the Middle East and Gulf regions,
expressing their support for a peaceful settlement of the
conflicts through regional and international efforts.
</P>
<P>
The Russian official said that Iran-Russia relations can
significantly contribute to regional stability under the existing
difficult regional and international conditions.
</P>
<P>
He said "Russia and Iran opt for an arms-free zone in the
Middle East and have signed the Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty
(NPT)."
</P>
<P>
While promoting bilateral ties, Iran and Russia have made
upon joint efforts to resolve the crises in Tajikistan and
Afghanistan, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said, "Bilateral relations are beneficial for both
countries and play a significant role in resolving regional
crises."
</P>
<P>
As to the cooperation between Iran and Russia, he said, "Our
cooperation with Iran is based on pragmatism without intending to
trample the interests of any other countries." 
