<DATE_TIME> 1996-10-24 13:52 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France to Provide Jordan with Soft Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Jordan and France signed here
today a financial protocol under which the kingdom will receive
80 million French francs (about 16 million U.S. dollars) in soft
loans.
</P>
<P>
Paris also granted Amman about 10 million francs (about 2
million dollars) to finance a project to computerized the Amman
Financial Market.
</P>
<P>
Agreements were also reached to provide Jordan with technical
assistance to finance other technical studies and projects upon
the request of Jordan.
</P>
<P>
Also today, the two sides held a meeting to discuss bilateral
economic cooperation and trade ties.
</P>
<P>
The two sides stressed the need for boosting their ties for
the benefits of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Speaking after the meeting, Jordanian Minister of Industry and
Trade Ali Abul Ragheb said he asked the French government to
support Jordan's efforts to join the World Trade Organization
(WTO). 
</P>
</TEXT>
