<DATE_TIME> 1996-10-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> AsiaSat-3 to be launched next year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 24 (Xinhua) -- The AsiaSat-3 satellite will be
launched in November next year, Chen Liqun, general manager of
China branch of Asia Satellite Telecommunications Company
(ASIASAT), announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The launching has been planned after the successful launchings
of AsiaSat-1 and AsiaSat-2.
</P>
<P>
According to Chen, AsiaSat-3 will replace AsiaSat-1, with
advantages in terms of life span and technology.
</P>
<P>
Chen made the remark at a three-day ASIASAT second Chinese
user's Conference, which is being held in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
ASIASAT was founded in February 1988 in Hong Kong, jointly run
by China International Trust and Investment Corporation, Cable and
Wireless Plc of Britain, and Hutchison Whampoa Ltd of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The consortium was listed respectively on New York and
Hong Kong stock exchanges in June this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
