<DATE_TIME> 1996-10-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian Former PM Rao Summoned by Court Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Indian former prime minister
P.V. Narasimha Rao was re-summoned by a Delhi court today to
personally appear before the special court at Vigyan Bhawan
(international meeting center) in New Delhi on November 6 for his
involvement in a cheating case of 100,000 US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the Delhi court had summoned him to appear in person
in Tis Hazari court premises on September 30.
</P>
<P>
The Delhi police and the Special Protection Group (SPG)
responsible for the security of the prime minister and former
prime ministers made a petition to the Supreme Court for a change
in the trial venue as Tis Hazari court complex was not considered
to be a safe place.
</P>
<P>
The Supreme Court, therefore, directed the Delhi High Court to
select a new place for the trial of Rao within the New Delhi
security zone.
</P>
<P>
Rao, who is also an accused in the St. Kitts forgery case, has
been exempted from personal appearance in this case scheduled to
come up for hearing at the new venue on October 30.
</P>
<P>
The stage has been set for the trial of Rao, who is facing
charges of cheating and forgery. He will be the first former
prime minister in India's history to be hauled up before a court
on charges of this nature.  
</P>
</TEXT>
