<HEADLINE> U.S. Grants Economic Aid to Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Addis Ababa, October 24 (Xinhua) -- The United States today
agreed to grant 29.7 million U.S. Dollars of economic aid to
Ethiopia, according to an agreement signed here today.
</P>
<P>
Out of the total amount, 14 million U.S. Dollars is allocated
to improve primary education systems, 9.6 million U.S. Dollars
will be used for improving the health services, 4.9 million U.S.
Dollars for enhancing food security, and the remaining 1.2
million U.S. Dollars for building democratic institutions and
civil service reforms.
</P>
<P>
"This represents the last of the assistance provided by the
United States to Ethiopia during our fiscal year 1996. Total U.S.
assistance for this year is about 90 million U.S. Dollars,
including development assistance and food aid," said a statement
issued by the U.S. Embassy in Addis Ababa today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
