<DATE_TIME> 1996-10-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNA-China Urges US to Pay Membership Due </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 24 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Association
of China (UNA-China) supports the World Federation of the UNA's
(WFUNA) proposition for settling the UN's current financial
crisis, its President Xie Qimei said today.
</P>
<P>
Xie was speaking in Beijing at a function marking United
Nations Day.
</P>
<P>
UNA-China is a member of WFUNA, which is the world's only
non-governmental organization dedicated entirely to supporting the
UN.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Xie also called on the governments of all
UN member states, particularly the US government, to fulfill their
membership obligations under the UN Charter, by promptly and fully
paying their membership dues and peace keeping assessments.
</P>
<P>
All member states should take part with a practical attitude in
negotiations on financial reform, conducted by the UN General
Assembly, and reach an early agreement on a reform program to lift
the UN out of the present crisis, Xie proposed.
</P>
<P>
Although the UN is faced with many difficulties at the moment,
it's founding was a wise choice by mankind after drawing painful
historical lessons, Xie stressed, adding that UN membership had
increased from 51 to 185.
</P>
<P>
During the past few years, UNA-China had been given the "Peace
Messenger Award" by the UN Secretary General Boutros Boutros-Ghali
in 1988, in recognition of its contribution to peace. It has also
been active domestically in initiating mass activities in support
of UN endeavors for peace and development, noted Xie.
</P>
<P>
He said the purpose of holding the function today was to
propagate the spirit of the UN Charter, to give the 1.2 billion
Chinese people a better understanding of the UN.
</P>
<P>
In the future, UNA-China is ready to strengthen and increase
cooperation with concerned organizations, by increasing publicity
on the UN, and make greater efforts to promote the cause of peace
and development, Xie said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
