<HEADLINE> Changshu Port Opens to Foreign Vessels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Changshu Port, a project
matched to the Singaporean-invested industrial park in east
China's Suzhou City, today formally opened to foreign vessels
after state appraisal.
</P>
<P>
In response to the opening and development of Shanghai's Pudong
New Area, Changshu has implemented a strategy of "invigorating the
city through building ports".
</P>
<P>
After several years of hard work, the construction of ports in
Changshu have taken shape.
</P>
<P>
A 35,000-ton container berth, and two multi-purpose berths for
the first phase of the Xinghua Wharf, jointly invested by China
and Singapore, have been completed.
</P>
<P>
Huarun Wharf, jointly invested by China and Hong Kong, is able
to accommodate 5,000 dwt ships, and handle 300,000 tons of cargo
annually.
</P>
<P>
Changshu Power Plant's coal wharf, which has been put into use,
is able to accommodate two 35,000 dwt ships at the same time.
</P>
