<HEADLINE> China to Publish New Edition of Lu Xun's Works </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 24 (Xinhua) -- The People's Literature
Publishing House in Beijing is to publish a new edition of Lu
Xun's Complete Works.
</P>
<P>
The event is to commemorate the 60th anniversary of the death
of Lu Xun, who is known as a great Chinese thinker, revolutionary
and man of letters.
</P>
<P>
The 50-year old publishing house has published a number of
editions of Lu Xun's complete works since the first in 1981.
</P>
<P>
The works of Lu Xun have been warmly received by readers
worldwide in recent years, resulting in a good sale of his books.
</P>
<P>
Chen Laiyu, vice-chairman of the Research Institute on Lu Xun,
said that as a pioneer of China's new literature reform, Lu not
only made trail-blazing achievements in the fields of fiction,
prose and poetry, but is also seen as the spiritual beacon of the
Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
Lu's sharp opinions on social changes is still meaningful at
present, he added.
</P>
<P>
Lu Xun was born in 1881 in east China's Zhejiang Province. He
wrote a number of works, which are regarded as an important part
of Chinese culture.  
</P>
</TEXT>
