<HEADLINE> Australian Stock Market Surges To New High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 24 (Xinhua) -- The Australian stock market
surged to a new high in the expectation of an interest rate cut
today.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index surged 30.9 points, or 1.32 percent,
to 2377.6, the highest close in history.
</P>
<P>
The local bourse set consecutive records earlier this month. It
broke through the crucial resistance level of 2300 points in the
beginning of October and reached an all-time-high of 2363.3 points
on October 14.
</P>
<P>
Weak wage increase, coupled with benign inflation figures,
heightened hopes of an interest rate cut by the Reserve Bank of
Australia.
</P>
<P>
Lower interest rates will make investment in equities more
attractive, because it will reduce companies' borrowing cost and
boost consumer demand. Lower interest rates will also make
investment in stocks more profitable in terms of relative yield.
</P>
<P>
A bullish New York Stock Exchange and takeover activities in
local industries also added impetus to the bourse.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index soared 52.6 points, or 1.46 percent,
to 3663.5.
</P>
<P>
The all resources index rose 13.7 points to 1395.4.
</P>
<P>
National turnover totaled 392.09 million shares, valued at
861.13 million Australian dollars (680.29 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
On the Sydney Futures Exchange, the December share price index
contract jumped 30 points to 2394.0.  
</P>
</TEXT>
