<HEADLINE> Immigrants Healthier, More Law-Abiding Than </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Statistics have shown that
immigrants in Australia are generally healthier and less likely to
appear in courts and jails than the wider Australian community,
Immigration Affairs Minister Philip Ruddock said today.
</P>
<P>
"Immigrants as a class are healthier than Australians and less
represented in our hospitals and other health costs because they
are subjected to a health check before they come to Australia,"
Ruddock said in a program on ABC Radio.
</P>
<P>
He also dispelled theories that immigrants were responsible for
a higher crime rate.
</P>
<P>
The minister's remarks were clearly in response to the
Australians Against Further Immigration campaign that started
early this month, which put blames on immigrants for pollution,
traffic jams, unemployment, crime, the hospitals crisis.
</P>
<P>
Ruddock said that a "properly balanced" immigration program,
which the government was putting in place, meant immigrants would
have a higher employment rate than the Australian population as a
whole.
</P>
<P>
"If the program is balanced, if you have got relatively large
numbers of people coming to Australia with skills and capital,
they help Australia grow and create new job opportunities for
other Australians," he noted.
</P>
<P>
"In other words, it helps unemployment, rather than hinders it.
And in that sense it's beneficial. You need to be very careful in
the way to structure the immigration program if it's going to have
a positive impact on unemployment in Australia," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19961024.0127 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-10-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Investment in Pakistan Grows in 1995-96 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Real investment in Pakistan
increased 11.6 percent in 1995-96 compared with an increase of 2.9
percent in 1994-95 and a decline of 0.9 percent in 1993-94.
</P>
<P>
According to the annual report of the State Bank of Pakistan
(SBP) released in the southern port city of Karachi today,
large-scale manufacturing and electricity and gas recorded
significant increases in real investment.
</P>
<P>
Real investment in large-scale manufacturing, which accounted
for 18.1 percent of the real gross fixed investment in 1995-96,
grew 35.6 percent against a decline of 3.2 percent in 1994-95.
</P>
<P>
Real investment in the electricity and gas sector, with a share
of 20.2 percent in the real gross fixed investment, grew 24
percent in 1995-96 compared with the 19.5 percent in the preceding
year.
</P>
<P>
Investment in mining and quarrying and wholesale and retail
trade increased 33.2 and 9.4 percent respectively, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
However, real investment in construction declined 8.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
The SBP further stated that gross fixed investment in current
prices rose 21.5 percent to 390 billion rupees (10 billion US
dollars) during 1995-96, compared with an increase of 14.2 percent
in the preceding year.
</P>
<P>
The ratio of the gross fixed investment to the country's Gross
Domestic Product (GDP) at market prices rose from 17.1 percent in
1994-95 to 17.8 percent in 1995-96.
</P>
<P>
Private fixed investment at current prices showed a growth of
29.4 percent to 214.6 billion rupees (5 billion dollars) during
1995-96 compared with an increase of only 10.3 percent in the
preceding year.
</P>
<P>
Its share in the gross fixed investment rose from 51.7 percent
in 1994-95 to 55 percent in 1995-96. It rose from 8.9 percent of
the GDP in 1994-95 to 9.9 percent in 1995-96.
</P>
<P>
Public sector investment rose 13.1 percent in 1995-96 to 175.4
billion (4.4 billion dollars), compared with an increase of 18.8
percent a year earlier. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19961024.0128 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-10-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-US Relations Make Positive Progress: FM Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry
Spokesman Shen Guofang said today that Sino-US relations have made
positive progress, and there exist advantages for further
improvements in bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
He made the statement in Beijing this afternoon at a press
conference in response to a question concerning the forthcoming
visit to China by US Secretary of State Warren Christopher.
</P>
<P>
Shen said that Sino-US relations have recently made certain
positive progress, owing to the joint efforts by the two
countries. Bilateral cooperation and exchanges in trade and
economy, as well as other areas have been developed continually
and even expanded, he added.
</P>
<P>
There have also been increased visits by senior officials from
both sides, exploring the prospects of further cooperation in
various spheres, which meant, he said, the high-level visit
program agreed by the two countries is now proceeding step by step.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, despite problems and differences
still existing in Sino-US relations, generally speaking, the
atmosphere of bilateral ties are much improved, with even
advantages of further improvement in sight.
</P>
<P>
Shen noted that China is willing to promote dialogue, together
with the United States, to enhance consensus and cooperation,
making efforts to overcome various obstructions, and settling
various problems and diversities, in an aim to push forward
Sino-US relations in a healthy and steady direction.
</P>
<P>
Describing Warren Christopher's forthcoming visit to China as
important, the spokesman said China hopes the foreign ministers of
the two countries would conduct discussions on the prospects and
possibilities of bilateral cooperation in various fields, to boost
bilateral ties steadily.  
