spokesman said there were no changes in the schedule, and
confirmed that the operation was planned for mid-November.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin was preparing for the open heart surgery according to
plans, and doctors were of the opinion that his health was "quite
satisfactory," Yastrzhembsky noted.
</P>
<P>
He said some adjustments were made in the preparation after
Russian cardiologists visited Germany and the United
States. Russian medics received additional equipment from
U.S. Professor Michael DeBakey which would possibly be used in
preparation for the operation. 
