<HEADLINE> 25 Rebels Killed in Clashes in Southern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 24 (Xinhua) -- At least 25 rebels have been
killed in the hinterlands of Basilan province in the southern
Philippines as government troops entered the fourth day of
operations against armed men who attacked a military detachment in
the area.
</P>
<P>
Colonel Antonio Santos who was supervising the operations in
the province, was quoted by the Philippine News Agency as saying
today that the heavily armed rebels were members of the Moro
Islamic Liberation Front (MILF).
</P>
<P>
He said that more than 25 rebels had been killed with their
leader wounded. Although the military did not report any
casualties, a dozen soldiers have reportedly been airlifted to
nearby cities from the battlefield.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the MILF launched the attack in order to
get a chip in the coming peace talks with the government.
</P>
<P>
The MILF has been opposing the peace agreement signed between
the government and the Moro National Liberation Front (MNLF). With
many disgruntled MNLF members having defected to it, the MILF has
become the biggest rebel group in the country. 
</P>
