<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Aims to Be Regional Center of World Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Macao is making efforts to become
a regional center of world trade, a top Macao government official
said today.
</P>
<P>
Vitor Rodrigues Pessoa, secretary for economy and coordination
of the Macao government, said at a seminar that it has been the
objective of the government to make Macao a platform for
international trade in the region.
</P>
<P>
"The government has been working hard to enhance Macao's role
as an international trading post in the region, and make Macao a
platform for world entrepreneurs to exercise their strategy," he
said.
</P>
<P>
The secretary said the government has been making efforts in
many aspects, including the introduction of an open liberal
economy and the improvement of the investment environment.
</P>
<P>
The Macao government has adopted the policy to allow free flow
of capital and goods, levy lower taxes and tariffs and fix the
exchange rate between the local currency pataca and the Hong Kong
dollar.
</P>
<P>
In addition, transportation and telecommunications facilities
in Macao have been updated.
</P>
<P>
The Macao International Airport, which was inaugurated last
November, has brought about a rise of local tourism and relevant
industries, he said.
</P>
<P>
Telecommunications facility in Macao has become one of the most
advanced in the world. International direct dialing telephone
service is now available to 219 countries and regions around the
world, and the number of Internet users has been growing fast in
Macao.
</P>
<P>
Macao is also training personnel to meet the demand in such
fields as law, engineering, enterprise management, trade and
tourism.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that Macao's role of a trading post is based on
such favorable conditions as its vicinity to China's Guangdong
Province and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"The role of a trading center is closely related to China's
open policy," he said. "China has a huge consumption market and is
also an important producer. Macao can function as a bridge between
China and the rest of the world in trade, finance and labor."
</P>
</TEXT>
