<HEADLINE> Tianjin Closes Down 89 Heavily Polluting Plants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin has decided to close
down 89 rural plants that cause heavy pollution. Their business
licenses will be revoked by the city's industrial and commercial
authorities.
</P>
<P>
The plants share a common feature of severe pollution and low
economic efficiency, according to the municipal environmental
protection bureau.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show the 89 plants were responsible for 25 percent
of the total water contamination caused by the city's 10,000-plus
rural enterprises, while their output value accounts for only 0.2
percent of the total rural industrial sector.
</P>
<P>
The municipal government has demanded that departments
concerned strictly implement a State Council decision on
environmental protection to prevent and control water
contamination along the Haihe river, by striving to reach the
target for total amounts of waste discharged into the river and
its tributaries.
</P>
<P>
It has also demanded district and county authorities to revoke
the business licenses of heavily polluting enterprises, stop
energy and water supplies to them, and dismantle the equipment and
seal up raw materials in the plants.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin is carrying out a trans-century green program, which
involves 28 projects in prevention and control of industrial
pollution, and protection of natural ecological systems and
regional environment. The program is estimated to cost about 10
billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
