<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, October 24 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar government has
launched a national greening project for nine districts in central
Myanmar, a Myanma official said here today.
</P>
<P>
The remarks were made by Minister for Forestry Chit Swe in his
keynote address at a two-day national awareness seminar during the
convention on combating desertification, which was commenced here
today.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar has rich resources in forestry and although there is no
area in Myanmar that can be strictly called a sandy desert, the
central part of the country is hot and dry and is referred to as
the dry zone.
</P>
<P>
