out for a total area of over 13,749 hectares in central Myanmar in
the 1995-96 fiscal year ended March 31.
</P>
<P>
At the seminar, Myanmar Minister for Foreign Affairs U Ohn
Gyaw, who is also chairman of the National Commission for
Environment Affairs (NCEA), said that the NCEA always welcomes an
opportunity to promote environmental awareness in the country.
</P>
<P>
The seminar, jointly organized by the NCEA and the Interim
Secretariat of the convention on combating desertification, is
aimed at promoting greater understanding and appreciation of the
convention on combating desertification.  
