STOCKHOLM -- Labor Party leader Thorbjoern Jagland will succeed
Gro Harlem Brundtland, the most influential figure in Norwegian
politics, on Friday as Norway's new prime minister.
</P>
<P>
Brundtland, who has dominated the Scandinavian country's
politics for the past 15 years, announced Wednesday that she was
stepping down.
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russian security chief Ivan Rybkin met the head of
the Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE)
mission in Chechnya, Tim Guldimann, to discuss a peaceful Chechen
settlement.
</P>
<P>
In the one-hour meeting, they decided to improve cooperation
between the Russian president's plenipotentiary in Chechnya and
the newly formed United Commission. The latter comprises
representatives from Moscow and the Chechen separatist leadership,
the Itar-Tass news agency reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
