<HEADLINE> Share Prices Recover Steadily on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Share prices finished mixed
on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index recovered steadily to gain another 13.16 points to close at
2,059.61 today.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume was 103.95 million units, valued at 219.18
million Singapore dollars (about 156.56 million US dollars).
Declines overtook advances by 210 to 147, while 221 other counters
remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Uraco was the most actively traded stock as it posted a
turnover of 7.34 million units. It was followed by SMB United
which had 6.49 million shares traded. Sunright was next with 5.66
million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
YTL Corporation led the gainers as it soared 1.6 Singapore
dollars to finish at 8.4 Singapore dollars. The City Development
rose 40 cents to 11.4 Singapore dollars, while the Singapore Press
Holdings (SPH) Foreign, City Development warrant98, and Cycle &AMP;
Carriage (C&AMP;C) each gained 30 cents to close at 24.2, 8.5 and 14.3
Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
GE Life and Samanda Holdings were the biggest losers of the day
as they declined 40 cents to end at 24.6 and 8.6 Singapore dollars
respectively. Tasek Cement was 20 cents lower at 3.9 Singapore
dollars, while BerLei fell 13 cents to 0.61 Singapore dollar.
</P>
