<HEADLINE> 140 Drug Abusers Nabbed in Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 24 (Xinhua) -- The Central Narcotics Bureau
of Singapore has detained some 140 people in an islandwide
operation to round up street-level drug pushers and addicts, the
local television reported today.
</P>
<P>
It said that 63 of those detained tested positive for
controlled drugs like cannabis, ecstasy and opium, and close to 50
of them were later referred to the Drug Rehabilitation Center.
</P>
<P>
Two suspected drug traffickers were arrested in the 19-hour
raid that began across the country Wednesday morning, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
The Central Narcotics Bureau also raided several night-spots
where five persons tested positive for cannabis and ecstasy.
</P>
<P>
The report said that 15 others who tested positive for cannabis
and ecstasy were out on bail but police said that they would be
charged in court if further tests show up positive.  
</P>
