<HEADLINE> French President Arrives in Jordan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, October 23 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
arrived here today for an official visit to the Kingdom amid high
hopes of an effective French role in the Middle East peace
process and stronger relations with Jordan.
</P>
<P>
Chirac, who arrived in Amman from the West Bank town of
Ramallah as part of his one-week regional tour, will confer with
King Hussein of Jordan in a one-to-one meeting.
</P>
<P>
The French president, who has visited Syria, Israel, the
Palestinian self-rule territories, will address Jordan's
80-member Parliament Thursday before leaving for Lebanon. He was
also scheduled to visit Egypt.
</P>
<P>
His tour to the region is seen as a move to seek a new and
political role in the Middle East peace process for the European
Union (EU) countries, especially France.
</P>
<P>
However, Israel, especially under the leadership of the new
right-wing government, has resisted attempts to strengthen the
Europeans' hand in the region.
</P>
<P>
The Israelis have publicly expressed dissatisfaction over
recent political initiatives by Paris and other EU capitals.
</P>
<P>
Jordan had not only welcomed but had also urged for an
increased French and European role in the region.
</P>
<P>
"We think Europe should get involved in the region," said
Jordan's Ambassador to France Sharif Fawwaz Sharaf.
</P>
<P>
"I see no reason whatsoever for (any country) to try to
deprive Europe from having a role," he said.
</P>
<P>
During the French president's two-day visit, an 80 million
French francs (about 16 million U.S. dollars) financial protocol
will be signed between France and Jordan.
</P>
<P>
Total French assistance to Jordan this year is estimated at
400 million francs (about 80 million dollars) in addition to the
French aid through the EU which is estimated at 130 million
francs (about 26 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Chirac will leave Amman for Lebanon Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
