<HEADLINE> Austrian Speaker Ends Visit to Syria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, October 22 (Xinhua) -- President of the Austrian
National Council (Upper House of Parliament) Heinz Fischer left
here today, concluding his three-day visit to Syria.
</P>
<P>
During his stay, Fischer met with Syrian President Hafez
al-Assad. The meeting was attended by Syrian People's Assembly
(Parliament) Speaker Abdel Kader Kaddura and Austrian Ambassador
to Syria Rober Karass.
</P>
<P>
The two sides discussed the latest developments on the Middle
East peace process as well as ways of boosting bilateral ties
between Syria and Austria.
</P>
