<HEADLINE> Relations Between Nigeria, EU To Be Improved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Relations between Nigeria and members
of the European Union (EU) which soured in the wake of the Ogoni
crisis in November last year may witness improvement soon, the "New
Nigerian " reported today.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper said such an improvement was made after Nigerian
Foreign Minister Tom Ikimi's series of meetings with ambassordors of
major EU member countries in Abuja yesterday.
</P>
<P>
The Italian ambassador to Nigeria, Umberto Plaja reportedly said
after his meeting with Ikimi that he is satisfied with the progress
made so far in the implementation of the transition-to-civil-rule
program and the human situation in Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
Irish ambassador Brenden Mcmahon said the visit was a step towards
confidence building and the normalization of relations between EU and
Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerian-EU relations soured in November 1995 after Nigeria
hanged Ken Saro-Wiwa and eight other leaders of the Movement for the
Survival of Ogoni People.
</P>
<P>
Ikimi is expected to consult with more EU ambassadors
today, the newspaper added. 
</P>
