<HEADLINE> Computer Inquiry Service Provided on Beijing-Fuzhou Railway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Passengers on trains between
Beijing and Fuzhou can now obtain information on journey times and
stations along the line.
</P>
<P>
The information is fed through in-train computers.
</P>
<P>
The express, journeying between Beijing and the capital city of
east China's Fujian province, is the first to provide the service.
</P>
<P>
Train passengers only need to screen-touch the item they want
on the computer to get the information.
</P>
<P>
Information stored by the computers includes timetable of
departures and arrivals of the express, details of transfers to
other trains, names of stations and neighboring scenic sites along
the railway route. 
