Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- The weekly magazine Nature has published the first evidence
that the mad cow disease, or BSE, can be transmitted to a human
being. A team of British scientists at the Imperial College, led
by John Collinge, have found the "bio-chemical signature" in the
variant of the disease Creutzfeldt-Jakob, which has so far killed
15 people in Britain and France.
</P>
