Palestinians in the West Bank with all the protocol for an
independent state, by addressing their parliament and telling them
what they wanted to hear at a very tense moment they were
experiencing.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- For the first time, a link has been established between the
mad cow disease, or BSE, and the new variant of the
Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease, which has infected 15 people so
far. The scientific magazine Nature today published the results of
a study by a British team led by Professor John Collinge, which
has found the same bio-chemical signature in the brains of the
people who died of Creutzfeldt-Jokob and those of the animals
infected by the virus of BSE.
</P>
<P>
-- The British Airways, allied with the Bollore-Rivaud group of
France, will renew the French air company Air Liberte by injecting
500 million franc (100 million U.S. dollars) into the company.
Meanwhile, the Bollore-Rivaud will also invest 250 million francs
(50 million dollars) into the French air company.
</P>
<P>
British Airways will hold 70 percent of the shares of Air
Liberte, while Bollore-Rivaud will hold 30 percent. 
