<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Wang Lijuan is a cut above the
rest when it comes to the length of her hair. The Chinese mother's
locks stretch for an incredible 2.3 meters - the longest in China,
and possibly the world, experts believe
</P>
<P>
Wang, who lives in Shenyang, capital of northeast China's
Liaoning Province, has had record long hair since 1984, though her
hair has grown less and less.
</P>
<P>
Now her 17-year-old daughter's hair is growing and
growing. Wang says she wants her daughter to have record long
hair as well.
</P>
<P>
Experts can only scratch their heads when they try to explain
why Wang's hair has grow so long.
</P>
<P>
Wang has a normal life style, and likes to eat beef, mutton and
some salty dishes, according to the Yangcheng Evening News.
</P>
<P>
She always insists on washing her hair with flour and vinegar,
and refuses to use modern hair shampoos. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
