<DOCNO> XIE19961024.0201 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-10-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> APEC Leaders Urged to Endorse Network for Small Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Business executives from the
Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) today called on the APEC
leaders to endorse a proposal to establish a network for small and
medium enterprises (SMEs) by September next year.
</P>
<P>
In a 56-page report presented to Philippine President Fidel
Ramos, the APEC Business Advisory Council (ABAC) also called on
the APEC leaders to help address the financing needs of SMEs,
which account for some 90 percent of employment in the Asia
Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
The report said the APEC leaders should hold initial roundtable
discussions in their respective economies by bringing together all
relevant government agencies, banks, venture capital and credit
facilities for this endeavor.
</P>
<P>
ABAC Chairman Roberto Romulo, former Philippine foreign affairs
secretary and now chair of the Philippine long distance telephone
corporation, said the proposed APEC network for SMEs will serve as
a "network of networks in each economy" to pursue action programs
in areas needed by the SMEs.
</P>
<P>
He added that the network would pursue an initial action
program that focuses on four key areas, namely human resources
development, access to technology and information, access to
credit and capital, and access to market opportunities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
