<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian President Leonid
Kuchma arrived here this morning for "a working meeting" with his
Russian counterpart Boris Yeltsin on the Black Sea Fleet division
issues.
</P>
<P>
Before his departure from Kiev, Kuchma told reporters that he
was flying to Moscow this morning for a working visit designed to
support Yeltsin ahead of his forthcoming heart surgery and discuss
bilateral relations between Russia and Ukraine, according to
reports reaching here.
</P>
