<HEADLINE> Rural Industrial Growth In East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Rural and township enterprises
in southeast China's Fujian province had 201.5 billion yuan in
total output value in the first eight months of this year, a rise
of 24 percent over the same period last year, according to local
officials.
</P>
<P>
Industrial output value from the period amounted to 132.4
billion yuan, up 20 percent from last year's figure, because of
quick expansion in its scale.
</P>
<P>
The province now has 192 company groups, 24 of which have were
set up just this year. There are expected to be 100 rural
enterprises with 100 million yuan in total output each by the end
of the year.
</P>
<P>
Rural enterprises have increased the pace of technical
improvement, investing 2.24 billion yuan in it, since the
beginning of the year, a 40 percent increase over last year, with
1,130 major projects of technical improvements.
</P>
<P>
Local farmers have raised three billion yuan to set up 3,800
joint enterprises this year, while rural and township enterprises
had 34.63 billion yuan worth of export goods in the first eight
months, up 22 percent over last year.
</P>
<P>
Officials predict that rural and township enterprises will have
more than 300 billion yuan in total output value this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
