<HEADLINE> Pirated CDs Operation Shut Down in South China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 24 (Xinhua) -- A plant producing pirated
compact disks has been shut down in Panyu City near Guangzhou, the
capital of south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
More than 50,000 counterfeit CDs were found in the plant, which
was owned by a Hong Kong investor, according to officials with the
city's Industrial and Commercial Administration and Public
Security Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Imported CD-duplicating equipment in the plant that was worth
20 million yuan (2.4 million US dollars) was seized, disassembled,
and put into storage.
</P>
<P>
Sources say that this was the first time that such a large
operation with such advanced technology for CD pirating has been
found in the province. 
</P>
