<HEADLINE> Flood Control Headquarters for China's Largest River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, October 24 (Xinhua) -- The Yangtze River Flood Control
Headquarters had its inauguration in the large central Chinese
river port of Wuhan recently.
</P>
<P>
The headquarters, which has representatives from Hubei, Hunan,
Jiangxi, Anhui, Jiangsu, and Sichuan provinces, and Shanghai and
Chongqing cities, will be in charge of flood control and
drought-relief on the river.
</P>
<P>
It will be dealing with flood control, water and soil
conservation, and construction of waterworks on the river and its
tributaries.
</P>
<P>
The Yangtze covers a 180-sq-km area, which contains a third of
China's population. The annual gross agricultural and industrial
output value of products there accounts for 40 percent of the
nation's total. 
