<HEADLINE> Chinese Productive Fair Tale Writer Yuan Ke </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Yuan Ke, a world-renowned
Chinese writer, has published more than 20 collections of fairy
tales totaling seven million characters in the past 50 years.
</P>
<P>
Yuan, 80, was born in Xinfan County in southwest China's
Sichuan Province. His first book of fairy tales was printed in
1947. He compiled the country's first book on ancient fairy tales
of the Han Nationality in 1950.
</P>
<P>
His works have been translated into many foreign languages,
including Russian, Japaneses, English, French, Spanish and Korean.
</P>
<P>
Over 150 scholars nationwide attended a seminar on Yuan and his
works in this capital city of Sichuan recently. 
