<DATE_TIME> 1996-10-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Radiation Processing Industry Takes Shape in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Radiation processing technology
in China has developed from laboratory research into
industrialization, according to a conference in Lanzhou, capital
of northwest China's Gansu Province.
</P>
<P>
The technique is conducted by exposing objects to gamma rays
emitted by radioactive isotopes, or electronic beams produced by
electronic accelerators.
</P>
<P>
The technique is widely used in seed breeding, petrochemicals,
medical sterilization, food storage and waste treatment.
</P>
<P>
The research of isotope and radiation technology in China
started in the 1950s. At present, China has 120 gamma ray
radiation facilities, and 46 electronic radiation accelerators.
</P>
<P>
The technique produced nearly one billion yuan worth of output
value in 1995, doubling that of 1993. Experts estimated the output
value produced by the technology in China in 2000 will be four
billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
