<HEADLINE> IFC Invests 37.5 Million U.S. Dollars in Shipping Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 23 (Xinhua) -- The International Finance
Corporation (IFC) today announced the approval of 37.5 million
U.S. dollars in loan and equity to finance a shipping company in
the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
The company to be financed is the holding company of Magsaysay
Lines Inc. of the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines mainly rely on shipping services for trade with
the outside world markets. Expansion of the fleet will lower
shipping and trade costs and enhance competitiveness. The
financing will help the Philippines' major inter-island shipping
company to expand its fleet in the international and regional
markets and reduce the age of the existing fleet.
</P>
<P>
IFC's financing includes a loan for its own account and a loan
to be syndicated with international commercial banks. In addition,
IFC, a member of the World Bank Group and the largest multilateral
source of equity and loan financing for private sectors in
developing countries, will provide a convertible loan and make an
equity investment in the company.
</P>
<P>
This is IFC's first shipping investment in the Philippines and
the first to be linked with privately funded and operated training
facilities for seamen. 
</P>
