than 190,000 tons, this year, a five-percent increase from last
year.
</P>
<P>
The north China region has a cold, arid climate with a short
frost-free period, which is not particularly suited to growing
fruit.
</P>
<P>
While it was working on increasing grain production, the
autonomous regional government also encouraged farmers to develop
fruits adapted to local natural conditions and to use more
scientific methods.
</P>
<P>
A survey has shown that the region harvested 180,000 tons of
fruit on 70,900 hectares of land last year. 
