<HEADLINE> Effective Measures Help South China Economic Zone (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Port construction,
heavy-industry, and enterprise reforms have given Zhuhai, one of
China's five special economic zones, rapid economic growth at the
beginning of the Ninth Five-Year Plan period (1996-2000).
</P>
<P>
In the first seven months of this year, according to
statistics, the zone, a coastal city in Guangdong Province, had
industrial output value of 18.6 billion yuan (about 2.3 billion US
dollars), up 20 percent from last year's figure.
</P>
<P>
To improve investment, Zhuhai has made a special effort in
harbor construction, building two 20,000-ton berths.
</P>
<P>
Following Hong Kong and Singapore investors, some oil giants
such as Mobil and Shell have built large oil facilities and
wharves, and experts predicted that in three to five years, the
city will become Southeast Asia's largest store and transfer
center for oil, natural gas, and chemical products.
</P>
<P>
An industrial development zone at Zhuhai's port for heavy
industry has become a favorite overseas investment venue,
attracting Sino-US investment of 300 million US dollars in PTA
projects to the 400-square-kilometer zone.
</P>
<P>
In the recent Guangdong provincial foreign economic and trade
fair, Zhuhai attracted up to 1.8 billion US dollars in foreign
investment, a third of the province's total.
</P>
<P>
Negotiations are underway on heavy industrial projects in
petrochemicals, construction materials, and shipbuilding.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19961024.0241 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-10-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Effective Measures For South China Economic Zone (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The city has had test-runs of joint stock enterprises, filing
for bankruptcy, and the trust system.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises with a good track record are being combined by
re-arranging assets into 19 enterprise groups, each with sales
pegged at more than one billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Some small and mid-sized stated-owned enterprises have
established a flexible legal person system to protect the value of
state-owned assets and to increase it.
</P>
<P>
A new social security system with medical and unemployment
insurance provides further guarantees for the operation of the
city's reforms.
</P>
<P>
Enterprisers in rural parts of Zhuhai had an output value of
five billion yuan (about 602 million US dollars) in the
January-July period, 15 percent greater the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The city has also made use of its location by co-operating with
neighboring Macao and Hong Kong in transportation projects.
</P>
<P>
The new customs building at Gongbei Port, which connects Zhuhai
with Macao, will open later this year, and preparations for a
bridge across the Lingding Sea, linking the city with Hong Kong,
are under way.  
