<HEADLINE> Lhasa Reports Record Grain, Oil Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Lhasa, the capital city of the
Tibet Autonomous Region, has produced a record 150 million kg of
grain and edible oil this year, an increase of 7.2 percent from
last year.
</P>
<P>
This year's record high is the result of greater input from
local farmers in agricultural development, according to a local
official.
</P>
<P>
So far this year, the local government has raised a total of
5.6 million yuan for farm production and has spent some 200,000
yuan spent combating natural disasters. More than 22,000 farmers
have received technical training since last year.
</P>
<P>
The official attributes the good harvest to the close attention
the local government and farmers pay to improving production,
making the most of farmers' initiative in building water control
projects and irrigating more than 3,000 hectares of farmland. More
than a million tons of manure have been collected to improve soil
quality.  
</P>
