<HEADLINE> Poeverty Relief Project to Relieve Hardships for Rural Women </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 24 (Xinhua) -- A poverty relief project is
helping more than 2,800 rural women's families become
self-sufficient by learning farming and family skills, according
to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The Happiness Project offers training and financial assistance
to women who lack the education and skills necessary to avoid
poverty.
</P>
<P>
The program plans to help China's 10,000 families rise from
poverty by the end of next year.
</P>
<P>
Organizers of the event are trying to raise money to support
that goal and plans to launch a nationwide publicity campaign
annually on Mother's Day (the second Sunday in May) as of next
year.
</P>
<P>
They hopes to collect 25 to 30 million yuan (about three to 3.6
million US dollars) next year, and the money will serve to help
extend the project to families in over 60 counties. By August,
they had received 7.65 million yuan from domestic and foreign
firms and individuals.
</P>
<P>
The project, currently available to women in provinces of
Anhui, Gansu, Guizhou, Shaanxi, Shandong and Sichuan, was launched
last year, aiming at family planning and poverty relief.
</P>
<P>
According to China Population Welfare Foundation, more than 15
million mothers in the country suffer from women's diseases and
about 90 percent of the same women have little education.  
</P>
