<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, October 23 (Xinhua) -- The Costa Rican Football
Federation has called on FIFA to ensure that the away game in
their World Cup elimination series against Gautemala takes place,
despite the deadly tragedy that befell the first encounter.
</P>
<P>
Seventy-nine people died and 125 were injured when overcrowding
caused a stampede before the two countries cancelled match at the
Mateo Flores stadium in Gautemala on October 16.
</P>
<P>
"We want the scheduled order of matches to be respected," said
Raul Chacon, member of the Costa Rican Football Federation's
executive committee.
</P>
<P>
"Gautemala must host us first, either in their own country or
in another place chosen by FIFA."
</P>
<P>
The return match in Costa Rica was scheduled for November 17.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rican football authorities say they intend to write to
the 1998 World Cup organizing committee to ensure that the
abandoned match in Gautemala is played before the return game.
