<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Leading Chinese film director
Chen Jialin has noted that the quality of Chinese films has
dropped in recent years due to a lack of qualified playwrights,
directors, actors and actresses, advanced technology and
sufficient funds.
</P>
<P>
Chen, famous for directing films on historical events, said
that in order to encourage playwrights to place great importance
on scriptwriting, many directors have planned to give awards for
good scripts.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the low quality of actors and actresses has added
to the deterioration of Chinese films.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, many actors and actresses were more concerned
with their images, and ignored the need to improve their
performing skills, he said.
</P>
<P>
To better emphasize traditional culture in Chinese films, the
filmmakers should invest more capital, and use a variety of
high-tech skills in their products, he said.  
