-- China's output of meat and eggs has maintained number one in
the world for four consecutive years since 1992.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that in 1995, the output of meat, eggs and milk
reached 52.6 million tons, 16.767 million tons and 6.728 million
tons respectively, more than 500 percent up over the respective
figures for 1978.
</P>
<P>
 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- China's gross domestic product (GDP) achieved "sustained and
moderate" growth throughout the first three quarters of 1996, amid
easing inflationary pressures and rising personal income.
</P>
<P>
