<HEADLINE> Singapore Now 2nd Largest Investor in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Singapore has overtaken
several Asian countries and regions to become the second largest
foreign investor in Vietnam and is well-positioned to place itself
in the top spot of the list after two major investment projects
are approved, the Business Times reported today.
</P>
<P>
It said Singapore investment in Vietnam stood at 2.4 billion US
dollars as at last month, while Taiwan was largest investor with
four billion US dollars committed mainly to light industry
projects.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Vietnamese officials as saying that two major
Singapore projects awaiting approval were worth a combined value
of about two billion US dollars, and when approved, they would
pitchfork Singapore into the top slot as the largest foreign
investor in the country.
</P>
<P>
The two projects include a massive tourism project spanning
5,000 hectares in the central highlands of Dalat, and a
development project of a new 150-hectare international town in Ho
Chi Minh City's Thuduc suburb.
</P>
<P>
Singapore investments in Vietnam soared to 1.7 billion US
dollars last year. This year, Singapore overtook Hong Kong and
South Korea to take the second spot. A hefty 61 percent of
Singapore investment is in the property sector, with the next
biggest sector being manufacturing, the report said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
