<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Eyes South Korea For Floriculture Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 24 (Xinhua)-- Sri Lanka is now targeting South
Korea for florictulture exports, Export Board sources said today.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka's floricuture exports have steadily increased from
32,000 US dollars in 1980 to 8.1 million dollars in 1995.
</P>
<P>
When Europe became commercially non-viable due to import
duties, Sri Lanka turned eastwards for markets. Sri Lankan
floriculture exports to Japan increased from 180,000 US dollars in
1990 to 1.66 million dollars in 1995, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
South Korea is another emerging market for Sri Lanka. Its
imports of floriculture from the country increased from 6.26
million US dollars in 1988 to 21 million dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
The sources added that with Sri Lanka being a closer supply
source to South Korea than many other countries, the potential for
growth is high.
</P>
<P>
At present, Sri Lanka is exporting to South Korea bulbs and
corms, live plants, cut flowers and cut foliage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
