<HEADLINE> Eight Slovaks Die in River Danube </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Eight crew members died and one
was seriously injured after a Slovakian cargo tugboat sank in the
River Danube near Vienna on Tuesday, media reports said.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of police and rescuers were sent in to search for the
men in what's been described as the most serious accident in
Austria for many years. Losses have been estimated at 700 million
Austrian shillings (65 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The tugboat sank after it got caught up in rapids in the river
swollen from heavy rain and crashed into the dam of the Freudenau
Power Plant. 
</P>
</TEXT>
