<HEADLINE> Agassi Beats Berasategui in Stuttgart Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Former world number one Andre
Agassi of the United States battled hard to beat Spain's Alberto
Berasategui 6-1, 7-6 (7/5) at the Stuttgart ATP tournament on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Agassi, seeded nine, reached a third-round meeting against
compatriot Richey Reneberg.
</P>
<P>
"I felt really good and hit the ball well. I could have played
one or two points better at the end, it was tough for me to put
it away," Agassi said.
</P>
<P>
He added that he will play only Stuttgart plus the Paris Indoor
at Bercy next week and hope that he earns enough points to claim a
qualifying spot in the eight-man ATP Tour finals in Hanover,
Germany, on November 19-24.
</P>
<P>
The 10th seed Marcelo Rios of Chile also had a tough battle as
he fought for two hours, seven minutes before taming Canadian
qualifier Sebastien Lareau 6-7 (4/7), 7-6 (7/4), 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Thomas Enqvist, the 12th seed from Sweden, eliminated German
Nicolas Kiefer 6-4, 6-4. American Todd Martin, the 11th seed, won
through into the third round on his fifth match point as he
secured a 7-6 (7/5), 7-5 victory over this year's French Open
finalist Michael Stich of Germany. 
</P>
</TEXT>
