<HEADLINE> Italy to Help Slovenia, Hungary Join EU and NATO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto
Dini said today that his country would try to help Slovenia and
Hungary join the European Union (EU) and NATO, local media
reported.
</P>
<P>
Dini made the offer during talks with visiting Slovenian
Foreign Minister Davorin Krakum and Hungarian Foreign Minister
Kovacs Laszlo about how to strengthen trilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said that Slovenia and Hungary would be among the first
group of countries to be taken in by the EU and NATO and that the
grouping formed by their three countries would be the only bridge
linking the economic and military blocs to central and eastern
Europe.
</P>
<P>
The three top diplomats also agreed to build a highway linking
the Italian port city Trieste, the Slovenian capital Ljubljana,
the Hungarian capital Budapest and the Ukrainian capital Kiev.
The road is seen as being of vital strategic importance to the
region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
