<HEADLINE>   Another Japanese Bank Opens Office in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Another Japanese bank, the Sanwa
Bank Ltd., has opened a representative office in Yangon, capital
of Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
The bank, which opened its office here Wednesday evening, is
one of the eight Japanese banks granted presence in Myanmar since
the country began to reform its financial and banking system,
opening its door to foreign investors.
</P>
<P>
The eight banks are Bank of Tokyo, Fuji Bank, Sumitomo Bank,
Tokai Bank, Sanwa Bank, Asahi Bank, Dai-Ichi Kangyo Bank and
Sakura Bank.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, 43 foreign banks have so far
been allowed to open representative offices in Myanmar. They are
from Bangladesh, Brunei, Cambodia, France, Hong Kong, Indonesia,
Japan, South Korea, Malaysia, the Netherlands, Singapore, Thailand
and Britain. Most of the offices are already in operation.
</P>
