<HEADLINE> Panama's Ports on Alert for Foreign Bank Robbers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Panama's ports and airports
have been put on alert for three foreign fugitives who took part
in a bank robbery on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The national police say the three -- a Venezuelan, a Colombian
and a Costa Rican -- have about 250,000 U.S. dollars on them and
must not be allowed to leave the country.
</P>
<P>
They are alleged to have been part of a gang of 13 men who
broke into the Banco del Istmo in Panama and stole more than
600,000 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Police arrested 10 of the robbers including seven Colombians,
two Venezuelans and a Panamanian and confiscated 350,000 dollars.
But the other three fled with about 250,000 dollars, the police
said.
</P>
<P>
According to police, the group had prepared for the heist for
five months and had managed to break into the bank without being
filmed by security cameras.
</P>
<P>
Panamanian authorities are now investigating the possible
connection between those involved in the bank robbery and a group
of Colombian guerrillas, a police source said.  
</P>
