<HEADLINE> Malaysian Company Eyes Air Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 24 (Xinhua) -- The Malaysian Industrial
Conglomerate Hicom (MICH) has shown interest in purchasing Sri
Lanka's national carrier Air Lanka, according to local trade
sources today.
</P>
<P>
The MICH has retained the services of the American consultancy
firm Gellman Research Associates (GRA) to advise on the purchase
of the airline. Three experts of the GRA are already in Colombo
looking into all aspects of the airline, the sources said.
</P>
