Air Lanka was recently advertised worldwide for sale by the
Public Enterprises Reforms Commission which has been conducting
meetings with other prospective international buyers.
</P>
<P>
Such meetings have been held so far in Dubai and Bangkok. The
next meeting will be in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Air Lanka, established in 1979, flies to 29 destinations in
Asia, the Middle East and Europe.  
