<HEADLINE> 59 More Erring Policemen Ousted in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 24 (Xinhua) -- Fifty nine more policemen have
been relieved from the service, bringing to 360 the total number
of law enforcers who have been fired since last April, local press
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Interior and Local Government Secretary Robert Barbers ordered
the dismissal of the 59 policemen in the latest batch of expulsion
of "misfits and scalawags" in the Philippine National Police
(PNP).
</P>
<P>
Of the 59 policemen, 25 went absent without leave to work
abroad. The National Police Commission found although they have
gone to the Middle East, Europe and the United States to find
jobs, they still continue to receive their salaries from the PNP.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-four other policemen were dismissed for various criminal
offenses such as murder, kidnapping, immorality and falsification
of public documents. The National Police Commission would file
criminal charges against some of them.
</P>
<P>
It was reported earlier that policemen had an unsavory
reputation in the Philippines. After assuming his post on April
16, Secretary Barbers began to reform the PNP and tried very hard
to refurbish the police image.  
</P>
</TEXT>
