that "supply-side Republicans created that catastrophe" of the
1980s.
</P>
<P>
Gore credited Clinton's economic policies with reducing
Minnesota's unemployment rate, creating new jobs and raising
family income, according to Associated Press.
</P>
<P>
Gore criticized Dole's proposed 15 percent tax cut, saying,
"They have proposed a risky scheme that would blow a hole in the
deficit and raise interest rates on mortgage payments for homes,
on car payments for automobiles, on everything that people pay
interest for."
</P>
<P>
Dole often tells voters that his tax plan is the right
prescription for a sluggish economy under Clinton, and that it
would put more money in the pockets of ordinary Americans.
</P>
<P>
Later, Gore stopped in Eagan, to promote Clinton's anti-crime
record.
</P>
<P>
"A lot of times we get together in America and see a problem
that desperately needs to be solved and we rush to some solution
that doesn't really get the job done," said Gore, surrounded by
uniformed police officers.
</P>
<P>
"This time we managed to do something right," he said. "We
coupled punishment with prevention and effective community
policing, the assault weapons ban, the Brady Bill, three strikes
and you're out, an approach that is based upon the real life
experiences of police officers, police chiefs, sheriffs, the whole
law enforcement community." 
