<HEADLINE> Pakistan Win 3 Athletics Golds in Islamic Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 23 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Olympian Shabana
Akhtar won the 100 and 200 meters dash gold medals in
International Islamic Women Invitational Games on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Akhtar sparkled in track and field by adding two gold medals to
her victories in long jump and 4x100 meters relay.
</P>
<P>
The diminutive athlete, who competed in the long jump event at
the Atlanta Olympics this summer, contributed almost half of
Pakistan's haul of nine gold medals.
</P>
<P>
In the 100 meters, led all the way to clock 11.50 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani Irum Khanum clinched the silver medal in 12.02
seconds and Loveli Begum of Bangladesh got bronze in 12.03.
</P>
<P>
The 100 meters final was participated in by eight athletes from
six countries, Azerbaijan, Bangladesh, Bosnia, Pakistan, Syria and
Tajikistan.
</P>
<P>
In 200 meters, Shabana Akhtar sprinted home first in 24.00
seconds, followed by Irum Khanum and Kojici Diana of Bosnia in
24.07 and 25.5 seconds respectively.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Bangladesh's Rohima Khanum Joothi won the 1,500
meters run.
</P>
<P>
Rohima's stamina in the middle distance race prevailed as she
clocked four minutes 48.10 seconds, while Dababaeva of Tajikistan
got the silver medal in 4:52.60.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani Shazia Hidayat finished third in 4:56.50.
</P>
<P>
Spearheaded by Akhtar, the Pakistani quartet won the 4x100
meters relay in 47.80 seconds, followed by Bangladesh in 49.6 and
Azerbaijan in 53.60.
</P>
<P>
Bosnia had won the 400 meters gold medal earlier in the morning.
</P>
<P>
The games, declared opened by Pakistani Prime Minister Benazir
Bhutto here last Saturday, attracted women athletes from 11 Muslim
countries. It is to end late Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
