<HEADLINE> China Has 110 Million Elder People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 24 (Xinhua) -- China has a total of 110
million elder people over the age of 60 and the figure is expected
to reach 130 million by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
By the end of this century, China will have an aging society
among its 1.2 billion population, including the 130 million who
will be aged 60 or over.
</P>
<P>
According to a seminar on elderly people, State Councillor Li
Guixian urged governments at all levels to make every effort to
protect the rights and interests of aging people.
</P>
<P>
A law protecting the elderly went into effect on October 1,
1996.
</P>
<P>
Li said the law, the first of its kind in the country, has
served to provide legal guarantees for the older people to enjoy
their old age.
</P>
<P>
Beijing, Shanghai and Tianjin have a high proportion of elderly
people among their population, with each city surpassing one
million.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
